thanks @vamega 

perhaps you could indicate your approval with an official review?

@baolsen @zhongjiajie any concerns remaining?

@zhongjiajie i know you initially had reservations, preferring to just replace pymssql immediately. do you feel better about this PR now that it is a generic ODBC hook which can also be used for MSSQL?  I like where we're at now because it is clearly a distinct hook that has wider use than MSSQL alone.  and introducing it alongside during a deprecation period gives users time to migrate should they choose to.  and it avoids a breaking change.

@potiuk 

Everything solved and build passes now.

Best regards
